Context: The Deafblind & Intervenor (C158) program is offered at George Brown College. There are information sessions available online to learn more about the program's content, career options upon graduation, and student life. Interested individuals can contact Cheryl Ramey, Program Co-ordinator, at cramey@georgebrown.ca to register for an info session. An previously recorded session is also available to watch online. The college's land acknowledgment can be learned more about on the website. Individuals can sign up to receive updates about application deadlines, college news, events, tours and more. The contact number for George Brown College is 416-415-2000 and TTY is 1-877-515-5559. The email address for general inquiries is ask.george@georgebrown.ca. The college's social media hub can be visited for further information. Please note that the information on the website is subject to change without notice. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
